        <div class="list-item">
          <li>
            <a href="https://archive.org">
            <h2>The Internet Archive</h2>
            </a>
            <!--paragraph describing the list item-->
             <p1> A non-profit digital library offering permanent access to historical collections that include multimedia content such as audio, video, and text as well as software and games. The organization was founded in 1996 with the mission of offering universal access to all knowledge.<br/>

The Internet Archive website <a href="https://www.archive.org">(www.archive.org)<a> has a vast collection of resources, including:<br/>
<!--categories archive.org has to offer -->
<h4><strong>A. <a href="#">The Wayback Machine</a></strong></h4> A digital archive of the World Wide Web that allows users to see snapshots of websites as they appeared in the past.<br/>

<h4><strong>B. <a href="#">Books</h4></strong>Over 2 million free books available for download or reading online.<br/>

<h4><strong>C. <a href="#">Videos</h4></strong>A collection of over 2 million videos including movies, documentaries, and news programs.<br/>
<strong><h4>D. <a href="#">Audio</h4></strong> A collection of over 2 million free audio files including music, lectures, and radio programs.<br/>

<strong><h4>E. <a href="#">Software</h4></strong> A collection of software and games that are either freeware, shareware, or abandonware.<br/>

<strong><h4>F.<a href="#">Images</h4></strong> A collection of over 2 million images including photographs, illustrations, and art.<br/>
In addition to these resources, Internet Archive also offers a range of services including lending books through their <a href="#">Open Library</a> project and hosting live music concerts through their <a href"#">Great Live Music Archive</a> project. Overall, Internet Archive provides a wealth of information and resources for people who are interested in preserving and accessing digital history.</p1>
          </li>
          </div>
          <!--End Section 1-Favorites List-Item 1 Container-->
